# Optional: custom domain for GitHub Pages
#
# To use a custom domain:
# 1. Rename this file to CNAME (no extension)
# 2. Replace the placeholder below with your domain
# 3. Configure your DNS: CNAME record pointing to monkey-d-luisi.github.io
# 4. Enable "Enforce HTTPS" in repo Settings → Pages
#
# Example content of the final CNAME file (one line, no hash):
#   vibe-flow.example.com
